Watch on youtube: https://youtu.be/JpTSzpRQ_T4 Tags: 3dprint , siraya , fdm vs sla , strength test , sla 3d printing , tenacious , material test , This video is a 3rd match of FDM vs SLA 3D printed bolts and screw nuts and in this comparison I am using SUNLU ABS vs Siraya Tenacious and Blu mix 50-50%. I will repeat all those experiments from 2nd match (tensile-, shear- and torque test) including impact and temperature tests too. Resin used in the video 50-50% mixture: https://siraya.tech/products/tenacious-by-siraya-tech-for-lcd-resin-printers-1kg https://siraya.tech/products/blu-by-siraya-tech-for-lcd-resin-printers-1kg 1st video FDM vs SLA (PLA vs water washable resin): https://youtu.be/k5xxZKv7IRg 2nd video Siraya Blu vs PETG https://youtu.be/7r16-UDo2t4 Other equipment used in video: Prusa MK3s (for printing without enclosure) Ender 3 V2 on banggood (affiliate) https://www.banggood.com/custlink/GGvh5E38Rt Upgraded, all upgrade videos: https://www.mytechfun.com/videos/ender3upgrade Creality small enclosure (affiliate): https://www.banggood.com/custlink/3KKEFjewOn Digital torque wrench (smallest 0.3-30 Nm - not the same, but similar) https://www.banggood.com/custlink/mD3hVIkGvv Contents: 0:00 Introduction 2:43 About ABS bolts 5:29 ABS in enclosure 6:50 About Tenacious+Blu bolts 8:08 Tensile test (bolts) 8:43 Shear test (bolts) 9:13 Pulling test (nuts) 9:57 Torque test (bolts) 11:43 Torque test (nuts) 13:08 Impact test 14:59 Temperature test 16:22 Conclusions #3dprinting #siraya #sla3dprinting #absfilament Download files: No downloadable files for this video.
